# lesson 5 box model

---



### reset

```css
* {
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}
```

browser has a default em and it change due to the rem you set, it is hard to control

`box-sizing: border-box` set to make the calculation easier

it calculate the whole box compare with `content-box` just calculate the content size

 

### basic box

![image-20231130122551207](.assets/image-20231130122551207.png)

#### margin

*the outside space of the box*



#### border 

*the outline of the box*



#### padding

*the space inside the box between the border and the content*



### margin

```css
margin: 1.5em;
or
margin-top:1.5em;
margin-left:1.5em;
margin-right:1.5em;
margin-bottom:1.5em;
or
margin: 1.5em 2em 2em;
/*in this case, the second number indicate left and right*/
or
margin: 1.5em 2em 2em 4em;
/*in top right bottom left*/

or
margin: 3rem auto; center it horizontally
```



### padding

same with margin 

```css
padding: 1.5em;
or
padding-top:1.5em;
padding-left:1.5em;
padding-right:1.5em;
padding-bottom:1.5em;
or
padding: 1.5em 2em 2em;
/*in this case, the second number indicate left and right*/
or
padding: 1.5em 2em 2em 4em;
/*in top right bottom left*/
```



### border

same

```css
border: dashed 1.5em red;
or
border-top: 5px solid green;
border-left: 10px dotted black;
border-right:1.5em;
border-bottom:1.5em;
or
border: 1.5em 2em 2em;
/*in this case, the second number indicate left and right*/
or
border: 1.5em 2em 2em 4em;
/*in top right bottom left*/

more specific
border-top-width: 5px;
border-top-style: dotted; 
border-top-color: blue;

border-radius: 50px; make a round angle not only for a circle
```

*   style

double, dotted, ridge, solid, outset



### outline

```css
outline: 5px solid purple;
outline-offset: -20px; to move it 
```









